race.comment: FASHIONABLE (9) has only raced twice and has been strong through the line on each occasion over shorter trips. By Savabeel so she will relish getting out to 1800m. Only concern is a lack of pace but Tim Clark will read the situation well and possibly roll forward. Nice staying filly in the making. TOMMY THUG (4) was a little one-paced when fresh from a spell last time out over 1500m at this track, just missing the placings. Has been in the money eight times from 15 runs so the patience is wearing thin. Needs this sort of trip second-up and should improve. THE BIG BLUE (3) beat all but the promising Golden Century over 1900m at Canterbury at his last run a month ago. Might lead and if left alone could prove tough to catch. WELCOME RED SUN (8) kicked this prep off with a couple of nice runs on heavy tracks then failed badly on a good surface at Kembla last time. Jury is out. LITTLE LUNCH (6) did little when resuming but did place second-up last prep so she can improve.
